Commentary.Commentary: Right then, the Aussies would look to take full toll of the advantage of their bowlers' good work. They will need a strong start and will need to fend off the attacks by the bowlers of India. Will the hosts start off strong or will India not let the openers settle down? We will find out as the Australian batting gets underway in a short while.

Australia's bowling was spot on as they kept things tight and hard making the batters work hard for runs. Starc, Cummins, Hazlewood and Lyon were all in the wickets. Starc and Cummins ended with a 4-fer and 3-fer respectively. Hazlewood and Lyon had a wicket too to their name.

After opting to bat, India were jolted early as they lost Shaw and Agarwal quickly but Pujara and Kohli dropped the anchor to start the revival act. The duo added 68 runs and just when it looked like Pujara-Kohli stand would go long and big, Pujara was sent back. Then came Kohli-Rahane stand of 88 that took them to safer shores as the Indian skipper went past his 23rd Test fifty too in the process. A mix up with his deputy though ended his stay and from then on, it was just one way traffic as wickets kept tumbling as India could amass just 244.
That brings an end to India's innings. They would feel that they could have added a lot more to their overnight score but it was not to be as Starc and Cummins wrapped up the tail quickly.

OUT! CAUGHT! Easiest of catches for Head! A very soft dismissal and India will be disappointed that they could not do much damage at the start of Day 2! They lose their last 4 wickets for just 11 runs! On a shorter length on middle, Shami just lets his bat hang in the way and it takes the splice of the bat. The ball lobs up towards short leg, where Head takes the simplest of catches. INDIA BOWLED OUT FOR 244.

FOUR! Something to cheer about for the Indian fans! On a good length on off, Bumrah drives this through cover-point and the ball races away to the ropes. He will be hoping to atleast cross the 250-run barrier for India.
Outside off, Jasprit has no issues in leaving this one alone.
On off on a good length, Bumrah looks to push this one away but does not connect bat with ball.
Outside off on a good length, left alone.
Mohammed Shami is the last man in for India.

OUT! CAUGHT! Starc gets his fourth wicket and India are nine wickets down now! Yadav threw his kitchen sink at this and in that process, loses his wicket. Starc dishes a good length ball on middle and off, Yadav looks for the big stroke again as he swings his bat hard but he does not time it well as it balloons towards the mid on region. Wade, the man at mid off, runs in, settles and takes a very good catch.
EDGY! A full ball on the pads, Yadav looks for the tuck away but closes the face of the bat early and the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the off side.
On a fuller length on off, Yadav strokes this through covers for a single.
SWING AND A MISS! Yadav is going for the big strokes! Back of a length ball on off and middle, Yadav swings his blade across the line but misses it completely.
Bouncer over middle, Yadav sits under this one.
SWING AND A MISS! On a shorter length and on off, Yadav looks to pull but misses.

FOUR! What an outstanding stroke! Yadav seems to want to add runs in a hurry! On a fuller length and on off, Yadav bangs this one over mid-wicket and it crosses the ropes on a couple of bounces for a boundary.
Bumper! A bouncer over middle, Yadav ducks under this one.
Good end to another over for Australia! Short and around off, Bumrah takes his eyes off as he gets away from the line of the attack.
An awkward way of blocking from Bumrah! Short of a good length and around off, Jasprit blocks it off his back foot with an open stance.
Length and around off, Bumrah plays a nice defensive stroke towards the off side.
Who walks in for the visitors now? It is Jasprit Bumrah who walks in with his blade in hand.

OUT! Another one bites the dust! Starc into the act now! That was a sucker delivery as he dishes a fuller one outside off, Saha's eyes lit up seeing the width as he goes for the drive. He though fails to get to the pitch of the ball as he drives away from the body. The ball goes off Saha's outside edge and settles into the mitts of Tim Paine. India falling apart here early.
On a length and around leg, Umesh tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Fuller and around off, Yadav strokes it back to the bowler off the inner half of the bat.
Who will partner Cummins from the other end? It will be Mitchell Starc. 19-4-49-2 are his figures so far.
Full and on middle, Umesh squeezes it towards cover-point for a run. A good over from Cummins comes to an end.
Another length ball that rises outside off, Yadav pushes it towards point.
Short of good length and around off, Yadav looks to poke at it but the ball rares from good length and goes past the outside edge.
Who walks in now? Umesh Yadav, it is.

OUT! CAUGHT! Cummins strikes early on day 2! Does well here as he pitches it full and in that channel around off, Ashwin walks a bit down the track and looks to push it but the ball just shapes away a hint to catch the outside edge of Ashwin's bat. It flies towards Tim Paine and he does the rest.
Back of a length ball around off, Ashwin stands on the back foot and pushes it to point.
Ohh! Cummins welcomes Ashwin with a Bumper! Short and around off, Ashwin does well to sway away from the line as he drops his wrists in the process.

We are all set for resumption on Day 2 as the two overnight batsmen for India, Ravichandran Ashwin and Wriddhiman Saha make their way out to the middle. They are followed by the Aussies who are also in readiness as they take their respective fielding positions. Pat Cummins will speed in for the hosts. 19-7-42-1 are his figures so far. Here we go...

Australia, on the other hand, would look to wrap the Indian innings as quickly as possible with minimal damage in terms of score and then try and bat it out as long as possible to wipe out the deficit quickly and then get a sizeable lead. How the game will pan out, we will get to know in a short while.

After a competitive Day 1, we are back for Day 2 as both India and Australia fight it out in the middle. Talking about the visitors, with just 4 wickets in hand and the score just 233, India would want Wriddhiman Saha and Ravichandran Ashwin to play it deep and long here. They would look to get close to the 300-run mark to make a match out of it.
... DAY 2, SESSION 1 ...

So that ends Day 1 as India finish it with six wickets down. Just four wickets in the bag, how many more runs can they add? Australia, on the other hand, would look to wrap it up as quickly as possible in the first session of Day 2. Do join us for Day 2 of the First Test at 1430 local (0400 GMT). Till then, cheers and take care.

For the Aussies, Mitchell Starc started the game with a bang as he bagged a wicket on the second ball of the game. Cummins and Hazlewood played a perfect foil to Starc as they kept their lines tight. So did the debutant, Cameron Green who also bowled brilliantly but still waits for his debut Test wicket. Nathan Lyon was the one on whom all the eyes were glued and he did not disappoint as he had a wicket to his name, that too of Cheteshwar Pujara. Overall, they would be pleased but would somewhere feel that after having India on the mat early, they let the momentum slip.

The Indian skipper along with his deputy kept of the ship afloat with a 88 run stand but then came the biggest mixup of the day and Kohli took a long walk back getting run out. With the second new ball coming into play, Neither Rahane nor Vihari lasted long as they both departed in quick succession. In the end, India would feel that they have thrown away the advantage here by losing quick wickets nearing the end of the day's play.

After opting to bat, India had the worst of the starts that they could have imagined as they lost Prithvi Shaw on the second ball of the game. Then came a small stand between Agarwal and Pujara. Just when Agarwal looked settled in for a big knock, Cummins sends him back. Then came a revival stand between Pujara and Kohli. The duo weathered the storm as they stitched 68 runs but just at the stroke of Tea, Pujara was sent packing and Kohli continued as he brought his fifty later.

An enthralling and engrossing day ends. All the talk of the pink ball Test between India and Australia lives up to the hype. Good competition between bat and ball. Australia would feel lucky to have edged slightly ahead of India by sending their skipper and his deputy back in the hut towards the end of the day.
Good length and just around off, moves away as Saha shoulders arms to get through the night. India end Day 1 with a total of 233/6 on the board. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 1.
Returns back to leaving the ball which is short and outside off. Just one ball to go.
FOUR! Fine shot! He gets width outside off and doesn't want to miss out on a scoring opportunity. Gets on his front foot and drives it through the cover region to find the fence.
Around off on a length, blocked.

Tight leave from Saha! He is trusting the bounce on the surface. This one is pitched short though and it is outside off. It jags back in sharply and goes over the middle stump as Saha allows it to go to the keeper.
Fuller and around off, Saha is on the front foot to block. 5 more balls to negotiate.
Angled in from around off, Ashwin looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Good length and around off, blocked.
Slipped on the pads, Ashwin looks to tuck it down the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pad and goes towards fine leg. Two leg byes taken.

FOUR! In the air... but wide. A short ball on middle, Ashwin looks to take on as he looks to pull but gets a top edge. The ball is to the right side of the man at deep square leg who tries to get around but fails to get there. A boundary in the end.
Length and around off, solid front foot defense back to the bowler by Ashwin.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Awkard bounce there? A length delivery around off, jumps a bit extra as Saha defends it by taking one hand off the handle of the bat.
Good length and around off, dabbed on the off side.
NO BALL! Saha gets one full and outside off, he squeezes it through the gap at gully and point. Two taken. And Hazlewood has overstepped as well so three to India.

Fine shot! Positive stuff form Ashwin here! He moves to 11 off 11 with this three. A fuller ball around off, he strokes it through mid on. The fielder gives it a chase and manages to save one as the batters run three.
On middle, worked through square leg for an easy run.
Length and around off, worked towards the short leg fielder. It was uppish but Saha played it with gentle hands.
Shortish and on middle, clipped down to deep square leg for a run.

Nicely bowled! Good end to the over from Cummins. Pitches it just ahead of good length and makes it to come back in from outside off to Saha who looks to block off the back foot but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Full and wide outside off, Saha looks to drive but ends up hitting it off the toe end towards mid off.
Shortish and around off, Ashwin pokes it towards cover-point and takes a run.
Length and around off, defended towards the cover region.
EDGY! Full and wide outside off, Ashwin goes for the drive but gets a thick outside edge that goes between gully and slip cordon. Two taken before the fielder can get to the ball.
Length ball around off, defended back to the bowler.
Pat Cummins comes back on. 17-7-35-1 from him so far.
A dot to end this over! Short of a length on middle, Vihari looks to block this one out but it goes through him into Paine's mitts. A good delivery to end the over.
On middle, clipped to deep square leg for a brace.
Shortish ball on the body, Ashwin swivels and pulls this towards fine leg but it is just short of Hazlewood who runs across and collects to keep this one down to just a single.
Couple this time for Ravichandran! A length ball on the off pole, Ashwin punches this one through mid off and Lyon gives chase and cleans up as the batters complete two runs.
PLAY AND A MISS! Back of a length ball outside off, Ashwin looks to cut this one away but gets beaten and Paine collects this one.
Down the leg side, Ashwin looks to work this to the on side but misses his flick.

Mild appeal now but turned down! Fuller and on the pads, Saha looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal but nothing from the umpire. Probably slipping down and maybe some bat too. End of a successful over from Josh.
Around off on a length, played gently towards the slip cordon.
Good leave! Good length and around off, comes back in as well but Saha is confident that this will go over as he shoulders arms.
Ashwin is up and running on the first ball. Fuller and around off, Ashwin drives it towards mid off for a single.
Who will come out to bat now? It will be Ravichandran Ashwin with the bat now. Can he along with Wriddhiman Saha see off the day for the visitors?

OUT! LBW! Another one bites the dust! Hazlewood gets his first wicket of the game. India in a spot of bother here. The second new ball is doing the trick for the Aussies. After dishing out a poor ball, Hazlewood bowls one on a perfect line and length. Vihari is stuck in his crease as he looks to defend but he misses and gets hit on the back pad. An appeal and once again the finger goes up. Vihari gets to his partner who probably tells him that he is dead in front and Vihari knows he has not got any willow so he walks off.

FOUR! SHOT! This is an anamoly from Hazlewood. It's a wide ball outside the off stump swinging away and Vihari leans into it and drives it sweetly through the point region. The fielder gives chase but to no avail.
Outside off on a length, left alone.
Good length and outside off on a length, left alone again by Saha.
Good length and on middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Good drive for nothing. Full and outside off, Saha drives it well but finds the point fielder.

NOT OUT! Missing the leg pole by some distance! Also, umpire's call on impact too. A good delivery from Starc though. He has got his tails up. Runs in and delivers a length ball around off and middle, it jags back in a little as Vihari tries to work it on the leg side. He misses to get rapped on the pad. The Aussies make a loud enquiry but the umpire turns it down. Paine goes for the DRS as he signals the 'T'. Replays roll in. There is no bat which is confirmed by the Ultra Edge and RTS. Time for the Ball Tracker. Impact umpire's call and the ball is missing the leg stump as well. So, Vihari is safe.
Australia review! Tim Paine wants to check this LBW appeal upstairs. It seems to be close. Let's see what the replays have to say.
Down the leg side, Vihari looks to glance it on the leg side but misses.
On off, blocked to the leg side.
EDGY! Again, takes the edge but is safe. A good length ball on off, Vihari looks to block but it takes the edge and goes towards point. The batters sneak in a run.
Outside off, left alone.

EDGY FOUR! Not the way that Vihari wanted to play that but as long as the runs keep flowing in, no one will care. On a good length on off, Vihari looks to tuck this one away but the ball takes the outside edge and flies through point to run away to the ropes. 200 up with this shot for India as well.
BEATEN! On a good length outside off, Vihari looks to block but gets beaten all ends up.
Short of a length ball and on off, Vihari looks to push this away to the leg side but misses to get hit high on the thigh pad.
Josh Hazlewood comes into the attack now. 16-6-25-0 from him so far.
On a good length on off, Saha blocks it out well.
On middle, blocked.
Wriddhiman Saha is the new man in.

A late review from India. Rahane was walking off but Vihari went running to his partner and asked him to go for it. Let's see if that is going to save the Indian vice-captain. Here comes the replays. No bat says the third umpire and adds that he doesn't need the Ultra Edge or RTS as it has clearly missed the bat. Looks like he has to keep walking. Yes. Ball Tracker arrives and it shows he is dead plumb.

OUT! LBW! That looked plumb to the naked eyes and Rahane was sure that he didn't get any bat and he was simply walking but Vihari went running towards him and asked him to go upstairs. A very full ball around middle, Rahane is rooted in his crease as he tries to keep it out but misses to get hit on the pad. They all appeal and the finger is raised quickly. Rahane knows he is a goner and he starts walking to the pavilion only to be stopped by Vihari who asks him to go for the review. The technology though won't save him as there is no willow and Ball Tracker shows three reds! Huge wicket!
Nicely driven! Fuller and around off, Vihari drives it to the left of the man at mid on who gives it a chase. Three taken before he can get to the ball and return it to the keeper.
Little full and just around off, defended towards the off side.
Starc is on money straightaway! Good length delivery around off, Vihari comes on the front foot and pushes it towards cover.

The second new ball gets due now. Will Australia take it straightaway? Or will they take it later? The Aussies take it straightway and it will be Mitchell Starc first up with the new ball. 16-3-41-1 from him so far.
Length on off, pushed to mid on. Just a single from this over.
Green goes back to bowling length and outside off, Rahane raises his willow to let this one through.
Bouncer outside off, Jinks sways away.
Good running and they get a quick single! A short ball on off, Vihari dabs this towards point and is quick to say yes to the single. Rahane this time, does not hesitate and they complete the run.
On off, blocked back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball outside off, Hanuma does not mind leaving this alone.
On off, blocked out.
Floated on off, Vihari punches this one through the cover region and will collect three. The fielder did well in the deep to dive and save a run for his side.
On off, blocked to short leg.
Loopy outside off, Vihari leaves it alone.
Flatter and on middle and leg, it goes off his pads to the leg side.
Short and on middle, clipped to deep square leg for a single.

EDGY! Does not carry to the slip cordon! Good length on off, Vihari looks to defend this one out but the ball kisses the outside edge and goes towards the slip cordon but reaches Marnus on the bounce. A good maiden over from Green comes to an end.
On a shortish length outside off, Hanuma raises his blade and lets this one through.
Outside off, left alone.
A stifled appeal from the Aussies! A back of a length ball on off, Vihari looks for the defensive push but gets beaten and Paine collects. There is a tame appeal but nothing from the umpire.
On middle, pushed out by Hanuma.
Short ball outside off, Vihari leaves this one alone.
Hanuma Vihari comes out to bat. After the unfortunate dismissal of his skipper, he comes out to the middle. Also, Cameron Green comes back into the attack now.

OUT! RUN OUT! Oh dear! Rahane has sold his partner down the river. Kohli's innings has been cut short. Floated around off, Rahane pushes it towards mid off and calls for a single. Kohli goes for it but Rahane after taking a couple of steps forward sends him back. Kohli is almost midway and he has to make a lot of ground to return. By that time, Hazlewood throws the ball to Lyon who takes the bails off. Kohli is not even in the frame. Terrible calling from the Kohli's deputy there. Massive wicket. The way Kohli was going, a hundred looked on the cards. A fine, fine innings from the skipper ends in a tragic way. Not much emotions shown by Kohli as he walks off but surely he must be fuming with the way he has been dismissed. Playing just the lone Test of the 4-match series, he would've loved to carry on.
Full and on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for one.
Rahane takes a quick single now as he works the flatter ball to the left of the short fine leg fielder.
Knocks the next fuller one to mid on and gets to the other end.
Tossed up and around off, Kohli lunges forward and blocks.
Flatter and on middle, clipped towards short fine leg.
Shortish and outside off, left alone this time.
Gets back to bowling length ball around off, pushed towards the off side.

SIX! BOOM! Enough of short balls and ducking under it, says Mr. Rahane. Cummins runs in and bangs it short and on middle, Rahane swivels and nails the pull over deep square leg for a maximum. Didn't hit it off the meat of the blade but it carried all the way so he won't care now.
Good length and around off, played towards the point fielder.
Shortish and around off, Rahane dabs it to the right side of the stumps. Thinks for the run but decides against it in the end.
Good length and around off, Rahane hops and blocks it out.
WIDE! A sharp bumper but goes well over. Wided.
Flatter and around off, Kohli gets deep in his crease to block off his back foot.
A single now as Rahane flicks the fuller ball around off and middle coming out of his crease. The ball goes to mid on and they take a quick single.
Shortish and around off, worked towards mid-wicket for nothing.
Flat and around off, worked towards the on side for a run.
FOUR! Classic Kohli! Full and wide outside off, Kohli nails the drive through the covers. That is a stunning stroke from Kohli and he enters into the 70s now.
Short and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for one.
Length and around off, Kohli keeps it out.
Pushes the next fuller one towards mid on and they change ends.

FOUR! Educated edge from Rahane this time. This is on a length and outside off, Rahane defends and while doing it, opens the bat face at the last second to get it past the second slip fielder. It goes well wide and into the fence at third man.

Edged but it doesn't carry! Lucky, Rahane is lucky. A fullish length ball around off, Rahane is drawn forward a touch as he looks to defend. Ends up getting an outside edge which goes towards the second slip fielder. It bounces just in front of the fielder. Ooohs and aaahs from the Aussies.
Just outside off on a length. Rahane covers his sticks and lets it be.
Good length ball just around off, poked towards the point fielder.

DRINKS! India are batting really well courtesy of their skipper, Kohli and Rahane. They will be hoping that they can continue on and not lose any more wickets in the last stretch of play for Day 1. While the hosts need a wicket and will need to break one of these two down. They also will have the new ball to work with and will be looking to scalp some more wickets before the end of the day.
Shortish and around off, clipped towards square leg for nothing by Kohli.
Full again, Kohli once again tucks it towards the mid-wicket region.
Full and on off, worked on the leg side.
Good stop and backward point. Short and wide outside off, Rahane cuts it nicely. The ball races towards the fence but the backward point fielder dives to his left to save runs. A single taken though.
Full and wide outside off, this time he strokes it to the left of the short cover fielder. Didn't hit it hard too as it won't go to the fence. They take two before the fielder gets to the ball.
Floated around off, Rahane prods forward and blocks it out.
Good length and around off, blocked off the front foot.
Edgy! Fuller and outside off, Rahane looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge that races past the diving fielder at slip. Three taken before the fielder can get to the ball.
Shortish and just outside off, poked towards point for nothing.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Full and wide outside off, Rahane offers no shot.
Shortish and around off, kept out.

ANOTHER NO BALL! Can you believe it? What are you doing Patto? Rahane blocks this length ball off the back foot. Once again the third umpire asks the on-field umpire to signal it a no ball as Cummins has stepped over the line once again.

NO BALL! PATTO HAS OVERSTEPPED! Full and angled on the pads of Kohli, Virat flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single. The third umpire asks the on-field umpire to signal no ball as Patto has overstepped here.

Short and outside off, slashed through backward point for a double. Oh but wait... the umpire wants to check if Virat's bat was fully in the crease as the run was taken. The umpires have a look and decide that the bat was short. Replays roll in and it looks like Kohli's bat was in. Poor stuff from the umpires.
Pat Cummins comes back on. 14-7-17-1 so far from him.

TWO BYES! Rahane missed it, and so did Paine! Flatter around off, spins in sharply, Rahane looks to fend this off but misses and so does the skipper of the hosts, Paine. It goes through towards fine leg and the batters collect two comfortably.
Short and on off, Rahane blocks this off his back foot.
On off, tucked to mid-wicket.
Shorter in length and around off, dabbed to point.
Flatter on off, spinning into the right-hander, Jinks tucks this to the leg side.
Nathan Lyon comes back on. 16-2-50-1 for him so far.
A maiden for Josh! Another good length ball outside the off pole, Virat is not interested in playing at this.
Outside off, Virat does not want to have a poke at this.
He does play at this length ball but the flick does not evade the man at mid-wicket.
Another back of a length ball outside off, another leave by the skipper.
Outside off, Kohli just raises his blade and leaves this.
On a length on off, Virat pushes this to the mid on region.
Play and a miss! Back of a length ball outside off, Rahane looks to cut again but is beaten.
SLASH AND A MISS! He had the width there but could not connect it. A short ball outside off, the bounce probably got a little too big on Rahane as he swings his blade at this but misses.
Outside off, left alone.

A good shot and Rahane will fetch two for his side! On a good length on off, Rahane prods forward and punches this through cover-point. The fielder gives it a chase and collects as the batters complete the second run.
Follows it up with a back of a length delivery on the off pole, Rahane dabs this to point and is quick to deny the single.
Outside off on a good length, Rahane is aware of his off stump as he does not engage at this one.
On a good length outside off. Kohli will leave this all day long. Let's this go.

FOUR! How's that for a solid response! Short ball to follow that jaffa from Josh and Virat is equal to the task! He swivels and pulls handsomely behind square leg for a magnificent boundary! The stunning boundary brings up 50-run stand between the skipper and his deputy. A solid partnership. 150 up as well.

Lovely from Hazlewood! How did that miss the edge? Lucky, Kohli is lucky to get away. Perfect line and length. He bowls it just behind good length. It is the knuckle ball from Josh. Rises extra as Kohli pokes at it to get beaten all ends up. Absolute ripper from Hazlewood.
Outside off stump and a tad fuller. Kohli skips in front and defends this confidently.
Similar line outside off stump and it leaves Kohli as he let's it fly past to Paine.
Good length ball outside off stump. Consistent lines from Josh. Kohli shoulders arms.
This one is a straight delivery on middle stump. Kohli defends it to the on side for a single.
Angling away outside off stump, leaves it alone.
A good length ball on off, Kohli looks to block this one out but it takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads.
Outside off, Kohli has no issues in leaving this one alone.
FOUR! Gets on top of the bounce and dispatches this one! Good batting this by the skipper! A short length ball on off, Kohli pulls this one through the mid-wicket region and collects a boundary.
Back of a length ball on the pads, Kohli clips this to the fine leg region for a brace.

NOT OUT! RAHANE IS SAVED WITH A DIVE! Quick single and it's extremely close! Hazlewood pitches this on a good length and Kohli defends this on the leg side and they take off for a run. Rahane responds to his skipper's call and runs to the danger end. The fielder from square leg has a shy at the striker's end and scores a bull eye as Ajinkya dives to make his ground. THe Aussies though are not too keen as the umpire's take it upstairs to check. Replays roll in and i looks like Rahane is fine with the dive. Yes, indeed he is fine after that full stretched dive. His heart would have come in his mouth there but safe in the end as a single results.

Run out check sent upstairs! It's touch and go for Rahane. Let's see what the replays have to show. Direct hits are always close but looks like here Rahane's dive has saved him. Indeed, yes he has his bat grounded when the bails come off.
Shiny side on the inside and he's looking for the reverse here. A good length ball that tails in and takes Kohli's inside edge onto the pad. A slight appeal but nothing to worry about.
Good length ball angling in towards middle stump. Kohli is looking to work this away to the leg side but it takes the outside edge and falls next to him. No harm done.
He's honing in on that off stump here with the line. But Kohli is equal to the task. Defended well.
Fuller this time outside off. Kohli drives this firmly to cover.
Good length ball well outside off stump. Kohli leaves it.
Gets his single this time! On a shortish length on off, Virat dabs it towards point for a run.
Shortish ball just outside off, dabbed by Kohli towards gully.
Short of a length and on off, again defended by Kohli.
On a good length around middle, defended straight by Kohli.

Short and wide outside off, Rahane gets on top of the bounce and hits it through the cover region. Lyon gives it a chase and does well to pull it in near the ropes. The onfield umpires want to confirm. After multiple replays, the third umpire deems it a clean save! Three for Rahane.
Short of length outside off, Rahane plays it towards point.
Good tight over from Hazlewood this. This one is angling in towards off stump and Virat defends off the front foot.
Pitching on middle and angling in to Kohli's pads. He flicks towards mid wicket.
Short ball outside off from Josh. Kohli sways out of the way.
Fuller on off stump, this time forces Kohli to defend. He rejects the offer of a run from Rahane.
On a length outside off stump and swinging in, easy for Kohli to leave.
Good length ball outside off. Virat leaves it alone.
Josh Hazlewood gets the ball now. 12-4-20-0 are his figures so far.
Just outside off on a good length, Rahane makes a leave now! Went to the keeper at a very good height.

One more single! Shortish and on middle, Kohli fends it off his back foot towards square leg for a run. Called leg bye which means Kohli failed to get bat on ball. He got into an awkard situation while playing at it.
Excellent run! Good length ball around off, Rahane taps it towards the off side. He takes a step for the run and Kohli is quick to agree. Easily done in the end.
Length ball outside off, stroked through point for a run.
Angling away from around middle, Kohli shoulders arms.
Shortish and around off, kept out.
Mitchell Starc comes back on.
FOUR! The broom comes out now. Rahane nails the sweep this time. It is tossed up and outside off, Rahane sits down and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.
On off, this time he keeps it out.

Floated around off, Rahane comes on the front foot and looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball lobs towards the short leg fielder who tries to catch as the Aussies show some excitement. Replays show there wasn't any bat.
Outside off again and full too. Rahane goes down for the sweep but misses to get hit on the pad.
Floated outside off, worked on the leg side for a run.
Tossed up just outside off, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Good single! Good length and around off, Kohli knocks it towards cover with soft hands and calls for the run. Rahane responds and they make it easily.
Length ball around off, Kohli defends it this time.
Back of a length ball on middle, Kohli sits under it.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
Length ball on middle, clipped through square leg for a single.
Ouch! Short and around off and middle, Rahane goes for the pull but misses to get hit on the body.

FIFTY FOR KOHLI! He has shown why he is rated one of the best in the world. Came in after the wicket of Agarwal, soaked in all the pressure early on and has kept the battle going. A length ball around off and middle, Kohli looks to defend but it goes to the leg side off the inner half towards square leg. They sneak the single. Kohli raises the bat to the crowd and his teammates. His 23rd half ton in this format. However, he will know that the job is not done yet and will look to keep grinding out in the middle.
Flat and around off, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
Short and wide again, Rahane cuts it again, this time it goes wide of the cover fielder who dives to stop but misses. Two taken before the sweeper can get to the ball.
Short and wide outside off, Rahane cuts but finds the cover fielder.
Flatter and on middle, tucked towards short fine leg.

EDGY! Lyon tosses it wide and bowls it full. Kohli goes for the big booming drive but ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball races towards the third man fence but the slip fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to three.
Shortish and on middle, turning in. Kohli lets it be as Paine collects the ball to his left.
Sharp bumper to end! This is just around off, Rahane does well to get out of the way of the firing line.
Length and just outside off, forced towards point for nothing.
Length ball angled in from around off, Rahane tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, Rahane shoulders arms.
A bouncer which goes well over the ducking Rahane.
Around off on a shortish length, pushed towards point.
Flatter and around middle, turned towards the leg side. Good over for the Indians as they get 10 off it.

FOUR! Kohli's time to show his class now! Tosses it up and bowls it full outside off, Kohli leans forward and nails the drive through the cover region. The fielder gives it a chase to the fence, dives to pull the ball back in but fails to do so.
Short and wide outside off. Rahane slaps it to the right of the cover fielder. Before Green can get around, they change end.
FOUR! Superb shot! First boundary for Rahane. A loopy ball and it is wide outside off, Rahane drills the drive through the cover region. No one is stopping this one.
Fuller and around off, Rahane once again comes on the front foot to defend it out.
Full and around off, pushed through mid on for a single.
A solid forward defense to end the over. Around off on a length, Rahane prods forward and blocks it.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the man at covers.
Little too straight from Cummins. Kohli tucks it towards square leg. Gets one but Rahane wants the second. Kohli says no.
Just behind good length and outside off, a leave from Kohli.

Fuller and just outside off, Kohli comes forward and looks to defend but gets a thickish outside edge towards the gully fielder. Soft hands from the Indian skipper means it goes to the fielder along the ground.
Slipped down the leg side. Kohli looks to flick but misses.
Pat Cummins comes back on to bowl now from the other end. 11-6-12-1 from him so far.
Loopy on off, Jinks is solid in his defense. Just a single in the first over after the Tea break.
Short on middle, Ajinkya pulls but finds the square leg fielder.
Short and outside the off pole, Rahane slashes at this but finds the man at point.
Around off, Rahane is solid in defense off the front foot.
Flatter and on middle, flicked to square leg for a quick single.
Beaten! Floated fuller and wide outside off, Rahane pokes at it but misses. Paine takes the bails off quickly but Rahane is in his crease.

We are back for the final session of the first day of the first Test. Ajinkya Rahane and Virat Kohli to resume the innings for India. The Aussies too are ready on the field. 35 overs remain in the day as the twilight comes in. 25 overs remain for the second new ball. Nathan Lyon to continue for now after the break.
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

With the lights and the new ball coming up it could be a tricky passage of play. How will things turn out with Kohli and his deputy out in the middle. India would hope for another partnership and a big one though. While the Aussies would look to take wickets and that too quickly to gain the upper hand. Can Rahane and Kohli deliver for India? Or will Australia rule the roost? All the answers coming up on the other side of the break.

Just when it looked like India will go into the break unscathed, Lyon produced a wicket out of nowhere to send India's number 3 batsman back into the hut. Australia, on the other hand, too have not let the Indian batters off the hook as they have made the batsmen work hard for every run and their this perseverance paid off in the form of Pujara's wicket.

An absorbing session of play comes to an end. India would be happy with the effort of both Pujara and Kohli as they both have done well to weather the storm. It never looked that India would stage a fightback after what transpired on the second ball of the game when Shaw saw his castle rattled but all applause to India's skipper and Pujara though. An even session of play by the looks of things.
A fuller one this time, Rahane comes on the front foot to keep it out. With this, time for TEA ON DAY 1.
Shortish and outside off, Kohli turns it wide of the man at mid on for a single to get to the other end. Last ball of the session coming up.
Shortish and just outside off, kept out off the back foot by Kohli.
A gift from Marnus. A high full toss. Rahane drives it down to deep cover for a single.
Flatter and around off, Rahane punches it towards cover. The fielder fumbles there but they don't go for the single.
Short and wide outside off, stroked to sweeper cover for a single.
A single to end the over! Floated full and outside off, Kohli comes on the front foot and pokes it towards cover-point. Calls for a single and keeps the strike for the next over.
Shortish and around off, Kohli blocks it on the right side of the short leg fielder.
Flatter and around off, worked on the leg side.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
This one is bowled full and outside off, Kohli gets on the front foot and blocks.
Fuller and around off, worked towards mid-wicket by Kohli.
Length ball around off, Kohli comes on the front foot and defends it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and around off, pushed towards cover by Rahane.
Gets behind the length of this ball and blocks it.
Back of a length and outside off, pushed towards point.
Outside off on a shortish length, easy leave for Rahane.
Flighted and on off, Rahane looks to block again but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the backward point region. A single is taken.
Loopy on middle, Rahane is again solid in fending this one out. Rahane is just testing the waters at this point.
Flatter and around off, Rahane goes back and dead bats it on the off side.
On off, defended off the front foot by Rahane.

Quick single! These two have a pretty good understanding of each others game and have been involved in so many good partnerships over the years and this single just tells why. Flatter and around off and middle, Kohli nudges it towards short fine leg and calls for a single. Rahane responds and gets to the other end quickly.
Floated around off, pushed towards the leg side.
Short again but this one is outside off. Rahane shoulders arms.
Good bumper just around off, Rahane sways out of the way.
Goes full and bowls it straight. Rahane flicks but finds mid-wicket.
This time Rahane pokes at this length ball outside off. Wants to get up and running early in his innings but is beaten here. Lovely line from Green for the new man.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Shortish and around middle and leg, clipped down to deep square leg for one.
On off, blocked out again by Rahane.
Flatter on off, blocked out by Rahane.
Ajinkya Rahane joins skipper, Virat Kohli out in the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT! Lyon takes the big fish and finally this partnership has been broken by the Aussies! Their resilience comes to an end and it looks like Lyon has the last laugh in his battle with Pujara! Lyon changes his pace this time and bowls a quicker one on off, Pujara is hurried into the defensive stroke but does not play it properly as it takes the pad and goes to the fielder at short leg, Labuschagne who takes a good catch. There is a loud appeal but the umpire is not flinching. Pujara seems to be walking back as well as he knows that he has nicked it. The Aussies go for this review. Hot Spot rolls in and there is a clear spot as the ball is close to the bat. The on-field decision will be reversed and Pujara has to go back now.

Review Time! Australia take the review for a catch against Cheteshwar Pujara. Lets see what the replays have to show. Firstly, it is a legal delivery as the front-on spin vision comes on. Looks to be some bat to the naked eye. Let's see what the Hot Spot has to show. Oh! There is a spot when the bat is close to the ball. The on-field decision is reversed as Pujara takes a long walk back.
Flatter and outside off, Pujara punches this one through the cover region for a brace. 100 up for the visitors. A gritty show by them so far.

Another appeal but no says the umpire! Flatter on the pads, Pujara looks to tuck this one away but misses and Paine collects and goes up in appeal. The umpire does not move and Australia do not want to go for the review.
Floated on off, Pujara lunges forward and pads this one away.
Fuller length ball outside off, Kohli comes forward and pushes it towards point.
Good length ball on the off stump, Kohli plays it nicely on the front foot towards cover.
Full ball on the leg stump, Pujara plays it fine towards the fine leg fielder for a single.
Full ball on middle and leg, Pujara flicks it nicely but can't beat the fielder at mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle and off, Pujara plays it with soft hands to the point fielder.
Good bumper to start the over. Short on middle and leg, Pujara ducks under it comfortably.

Shouts of 'Catch It' but it is not taken! There was definitely some bat there! Floated on off, Pujara tried to pad this one away but it took the pad, took some part of the bat and lobbed towards silly point, who tried to dive and take this but was not able to. The batters cross ends at the last ball of the over. Slightly expensive by Nathan as he concedes 9 runs off this over.
Flighted on middle, worked to the leg side yet again by Cheteshwar.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Pujara and this time he sends it through the on side! Good batting by Pujara! Floated on off, Pujara skips down the track and works this through mid-wicket and it fetches him another boundary.

FOUR! The length is a little too short and Pujara takes full toll of this one! Pujara continuing with his attacking approach against Lyon! Flatter and outside off, Pujara punches this one through the cover region to find the ropes.
Flatter and lands it around off, Pujara flicks this to square leg.
Short ball going down the leg side. Easy for Kohli, lets it be and ducks under it.
Short of a good length on middle, Kohli defends once again towards mid wicket.
Good length on middle, Kohli defends confidently on the leg side.

FOUR! Streaky but necessary for Virat! He's drawn into this fuller delivery and attempts a cover drive. It takes the outside edge and finds the gap between slip and gully for a boundary towards third man.
Shorter ball from Green. Kohli defends off the back foot.
Fuller and on off stump this time. Kohli defends down the ground.

No Ball! Green oversteps for the second time! Lands one on a length and outside off, Kohli watches it closely and then lifts his willow to let it be. The third umpire there calls a no ball as Green was well over his popping crease.
Floated on off, Kohli pushes this through the mid on region for a single.
Loopy on middle, Virat pushes this to the leg side.
Flatter delivery on off, Kohli blocks this one out.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
On middle, blocked.

IN THE AIR...SAFE! Pujara survives and India will be glad that he does! Flatter on off, spins back into the right-hander, Pujara looks for the tickle it down the leg side and clips it towards the leg slip. Labuschagne is the man there who dives to his left but it not able to catch it. The batters take a single. 50-run stand is up between Pujara and Kohli. A crucial one from India's point.
Good length ball outside off, Kohli plays it towards cover, thinks for the single but decides against it.
Length ball around off, Kohli has no intention to play that and shoulders arms.
Full ball on middle and leg, flicked away nicely in the gap towards square leg for a couple of runs.
Short of a length ball, Kohli tucks it on the leg side towards square leg.
Short ball outside off, Kohli stands tall and hits hard, but straight to the fielder at covers.
Shortish ball outside off, Kohli hops and dabs it down on the off side.
Cameron Green is back on for the hosts. 2-0-5-0 are his figures so far.
A dot to end the over! Flatter and outside off, Pujara lunges and puts his pad front but he makes no contact with the ball and the ball goes to Paine. Another great over by Nathan. Just 2 runs.
Short and on off, Pujji pushes this to the point region.
Flighted on off, Pujara pushes this to the leg side.
Loopy on off, Pujara again comes forward and blocks this off his pads and it lobs towards the cover region. An interesting battle between Lyon and Pujara is going on.
Floated on off, Pujara lunges forward and pads this away to the off side.
Full and wide outside off, Pujara drives it through cover-point and gets brace.

FOUR! There's the response from Kohli. Starc bangs it short and instead of sitting under it, Kohli plays a controlled pull shot. He gets on top of the bounce and then rolls his wrists as he pulls it wide of the mid-wicket fielder who gives it a chase but fails to stop.
Good leave! Just outside off on a good length, Kohli is confident about his off stump as he lets it be.
Another short one from Starc, Kohli pushes it towards point.

The physio is out in the middle now having a look at Kohli's thumb. He got stung hard on the thumb on the previous ball. But this is nothing that a warrior like Kohli can't shake off and he looks okay to continue.

Ouch! That would hurt! Had there been a forward short leg, it would've hurt the Indians and Kohli more. Shortish and angled in, Kohli looks to work it around the corner but ends up getting hit on the gloves. The ball lobs just away from the forward short leg position. There is no one there and mid-wicket has no chance to get around. Shake of the head from the Indian skipper.
Another back of a length ball around off, Kohli hops and blocks it out.
Back of a length and around off, Kohli pokes it towards point.

A mild appeal from the Aussies but nothing doing! Floated outside off, Pujara comes down the track and then pads it towards the silly point fielder who catches the ball and appeals. Not out says the umpire and no review from the Aussies.
Full and just outside off, Kohli flicks it wide of the man at mid-wicket gently and takes one.
Quicker one! Short and around off, pushed to the right of the bowler.
Flatter and around off and middle, turned towards square leg.
Around off again, Kohli gets on the front foot again to block.
Full and just outside off, Kohli gets a big stride forward to bunt it on the off side.
Good ball to end the over! Equally well defended by Pujara. This is very full and on the stumps, Pujara digs it back to the bowler.
Angled in from around off. It is shortish in length. Pujara does well to block off his back foot.
Around off on a good length, kept out again.
This one is around off on a length, he is solid behind the line of the ball to defend.
Just behind good length but outside off so Pujara does what he does best. Lets it go to the keeper.
Quick single! Kohli taps the good length ball towards point and calls for a single. Pujara responds this time and gets it easily in the end.

DRINKS! A steady start to the second session by the team from the sub-continent. They have started off well as they are yet to lose their two best batters, Pujara and Kohli. Both the batters are looking to attack Lyon while they are taking their chances against the Aussie quicks. These two are capable of taking the game away from the hosts and Australia will be looking to break this partnership.
Shortish and around off, Pujara comes down the track and then looks to block but the ball hits his pad and goes back to the bowler.
This one is outside off from Lyon. Pujara skips and pads this away.
Flatter and on middle and leg, worked towards square leg.
Floated ball on middle, Pujara plays it towards the leg side for no run.

An opportunity goes abegging! Floated ball on middle and leg, Pujara tries to flick but just manages to get an inside edge. The ball lobs towards short leg where the fielder tries to take the catch but fails to do so. Lucky for Pujara there.
Floated ball outside off stump, Pujara comes forward and pads it away on the off.
Tucks him up this time. It's on middle stump and just a tad shorter. Kohli jumps but blocks well off the back foot to end the over.
Short of a good length ball from Mitchell angling away, Kohli shoulders arms to this.
Length ball from Starc on off stump, Kohli defends.
There was one in it! It's fuller on off stump, Kohli defends this in a gap towards the cover region and is halfway down the pitch but Pujara says no.
Fuller and on off stump, Kohli drives confidently and times it well but straight to the fielder at cover.
Angling away from Kohli. He leaves this length ball alone.
A maiden from Lyon! Shortish and on middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Flat and around off, turns in a touch as Pujara works it towards deep square leg.
Little shortish and around off, poked to the left of Lyon.
Floated outside off, this time he defends it.
Good intent again from Pujara. He jumps out of his crease and gets to the pitch of the ball which is looped on middle, he whips it hard but fails to beat the man at mid-wicket.
Flatter and turning in, worked towards short fine leg.
Another one wide outside off, Kohli once again doesn't flirt with it and lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off on a good length, Kohli shoulders arms.
Full and on middle, Kohli flicks but finds mid-wicket.
Very full delivery on the middle stump. Virat does well to block it around point.
Short of a length ball on middle, defended straight by Kohli.
FOUR! Full ball on middle and leg, Virat flicks it in the gap through mid-wicket. Not a good start by Starc.
Flights it up nicely and lands it around off, Kohli strokes it through mid on for a single. A good over from Lyon. Just the single from it.
Short again and on middle, worked to the leg side.
Flatter on middle, Kohli tucks this to the man at short fine leg.
Good lines here from Nathan Lyon. He's keeping it tight this over. Kohli defends this ball on middle stump once again.
Flighted on off stump, well defended by Virat.

Good flight and drift from Lyon. An appeal from Lyon and Paine but nothing from the umpire. Lyon bowls a tossed up ball but the line is down the leg side, Kohli looks to nudge it fine down the leg side but misses it. There is an appeal from Paine for a caught behind but nothing from the umpire. Replays come in later and reckons that the umpire was right as the Hot Spot failed to pick anything there.
Good length bowling from Cummins to end the over. On middle again, Pujara, solid as a wall, blocks this.
Length ball on middle, Pujara defends to the leg side.
Outside off and fuller, front foot defence from Cheteshwar.
Shorter on middle stump. Pujara blocks solidly.
A couple now! Angling in from around off on a length from Cummins towards CP's pads. He clips it towards deep square leg where the fielder from fine leg runs to his left and saves a couple.
Good bumper from Cummins to start the over. Pujara ducks under it.
Another solid front foot defense from Kohli to end the over. 4 off it. Pujara tried to put pressure on Lyon in the first over while Kohli with that boundary has confirmed his approach.
Full again, pushed towards point.
Floated around off, Kohli is solid on his front foot again.
Flatter and around middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! BANG! Kohli doesn't want the spinner to settle either. Floated fuller and around off, Kohli jumps out of his crease and slams it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Floated fuller and around off, Kohli gets his front foot forward and pushes it towards cover.
Beaten! Yes, Pujara is beaten after a long time in this innings. This one is pitched just behind good length and is around off, Pujara has a hard push at it but is beaten.
Length and around off, Pujara keeps it out.
Shortish and around off, tucked towards square leg.
Sharp bouncer! Pujara sways away.
Around off on a good length, solid defense again from Pujara.
Good length and around off, blocked.
Flighted on off, Virat lunges forward and pokes it towards covers.

Loopy delivery around off, Pujara lunges forward and punches this one through the cover region. By the time, the fielder can run in and clean up in the deep, the batters collect three runs. Good intent from Pujara against the spinner.
Loopy on off, Pujara again strides forward and works this through the square leg region.
Floated on off, CP again steps out and looks to defend but the ball hits his pads and then hit bat and lobs towards the off side.
Short and on off, Pujara comes down the track and defends this one out with his pad.
Flatter around off, Pujara cuts this one through the backward point region for a couple. 'Catch it' was the cry from the fielders there.
Spin for the first time! Here's Nathan Lyon!
Shortish and around off, Kohli hops and pushes it towards point.
A bumper now but the line is little down the leg side. Virat sits under it.
In the channel outside off, Kohli lets it be.
Fuller and outside off, Kohli gets on the front foot and drives it through gully and point. One of the fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to two.
Shortish and outside off, Kohli offers no stroke to this one.
Length ball around off and middle, worked through square leg for a couple.

Nicely done! Hazlewood strays on the pads of Kohli. The Indian skipper tickles it towards fine leg. The deep square leg fielder comes around as the ball slows down as it nears the rope. Three taken. Well, Kohli had failed to get bat on it and it was called leg byes.
A slight misfield and Pujara sneaks a single. Fuller and around off, Pujara pushes it to the right side of the gully fielder who fails to make a clean stop. A run taken.
A bouncer now and Kohli pulls it by rolling his wrists. The ball goes to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller and around off, defended back to the bowler.
Good single! Good length and just outside off, Pujara pushes it towards backward point and calls for a quick single.
Fuller and around middle, driven to mid on.
Beaten with a lovely delivery. This one is on a perfect line and length. Just around off and on a good length. Kohli has to play at it. He does that and is beaten all ends up.
Nicely bowled! Kohli was surprised there. This one is angled from off and it comes back sharply as Kohli fends it off the gloves. The ball goes to fine leg and they scamper back for a couple.
Good length and around middle, clipped towards fine leg for a single.
This one is outside off on a good length. An easy leave this time.
Sharp bouncer from Cummins! Equally well left by Pujara. This one was pitched around off and then came back in nicely. It was at a good height too. Pujara does really well to sway away.
Good length and around off, a solid front foot defense from Pujara.
Just behind good length and around off, poked towards the point region. Kohli thinks for the single but Pujara says no.
Whipped nicely but Kohli can't beat mid on. Fuller and on the pads from Josh. Kohli flicks it nicely but the man at mid on moves to his right and stops the ball.
Fuller and around off, stroked to mid on.
Fullish one on middle and leg, Pujara flicks it through square leg and gets to the other end.
A bumper but it goes well over Pujara. He has no business with that as he sits under it.
Length ball around off, Pujara is solid in his defense.
Dot to end! Maiden to start the second session from Cummins too. A length ball around off, Kohli pushes it towards the gully fielder.
Length and outside off, an easy leave for Kohli.
Another one outside off, Kohli has his sticks covered as he lets it be.
Outside off, Kohli this time lets it be.

Just short! Lovely stuff from Cummins and he almost got the better of the Indian skipper there. A length ball around off and middle, Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but ends up getting an inside edge on the pad. The ball lobs just ahead of the forward short leg fielder. The fielder there dives forward and tries to catch but fails to get his fingers under the ball. Heart in the mouth moment for the Indian skipper there.

Good stop at third slip. A length ball just outside off, Kohli comes on the front foot and looks to defend with soft hands. Kohli ends up getting a thick outside edge. Labuschagne at third slip does really well to dive to his right and stop the ball.
Outside off, Pujara lets this one be. A maiden to start off the second session.
Back of a length and on off, Pujara pushes it to the mid on region.
Fuller and around middle, Pujara pushes it back to the bowler. He was trying to work it on the leg side but ended up poking it back.
Good length and outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Length and around off, pushed towards the cover region by Pujara.
Fullish and around middle to begin the session from Hazlewood. Pujara defends it towards the leg side.

Welcome back for the second session of Day 1 of the Pink Ball Test. The two unbeaten Indian batsmen, Cheteshwar Pujara and Indian skipper, Virat Kohli walk out to the middle. The Australian players too have taken their field. India would look to up the scoring in this session while Australia would look to send these two batting mainstays early to gain the upper hand. Who will take this session? Let's find out as Josh Hazlewood to start the first over after dinner.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

The start for India was not what they would have wanted but they did well to steady the ship after the blow early on. After Shaw fell, it was the duo of Agarwal and Pujara who played slow but kept battling it out against a good bowling show by the Aussies. Agarwal also was sent back and in came Kohli and now it is India's two best batters, Pujara and Kohli out there. India will hope that they stay out there for a longer time. It has been a very interesting session and it looks like the second session will be more of the same. Stay tuned for the second session...

Australia were right on the money, from the very first ball. Starc got rid of Shaw right on the 2nd ball of the day and India were already on the back foot right at the start. They were bowling on the right lines and lengths and have been very disciplined with the pink ball in hand. Cummins bowled a beauty to send Agarwal back to the shed. The hosts have done really well and will look to continue the same in the upcoming sessions.

We have witnessed a very well measured first session of play from both the teams. Australia were on the front foot at the start but then the Indian batting did well to claw back into the game, albeit slowly. Although, Australia would be the happier side at the end of the first session of play.
Good length ball around off, Kohli judges it well as he makes a leave. That will be DINNER ON DAY 1!
Another length ball on off, Kohli taps it to point.
Back of a length on off, Kohli keeps it out.
Green lands one outside off and Kohli does not fiddle with it.
Full and on the pads of VK, Kohli clips it towards deep mid-wicket and comes back for a second. Good running from both the batters.
Short one for Kohli and Virat is happy to sit under it.
Brilliantly bowled from Hazlewood! He lands one around off and on a length, Pujara does well to get his bat inside the line as he makes a leave.
Full and on middle and leg, Kohli flicks it towards deep mid-wicket and scampers for a single.
Another length ball outside off, Josh is playing with the patience of Kohli there as Virat lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Full and on off, Virat strokes it towards mid off this time.
Fuller and around off, Kohli makes another leave.
Length ball outside off, Kohli lets it be.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Short of a length on off, CP blocks it off.
On off on a good length, CP pushes this towards mid on and will collect a brace as the fielder chases after this and stops it.
On a length on off, Pujara fends this one back towards the bowler.
Outside off, Pujara lofts his bat and lets this one to Paine.
On middle, pushed to the mid on region.

A short ball on middle, Pujji hops and blocks this one near the man at short leg. The umpire also calls this as a No Ball as Green had overstepped. Not the kind of start Green would have wanted on his debut.
The debutant, Cameron Green is introduced into the attack.
Good length and around off, Pujara taps it between cover and point to take a quick run.
Length ball around off, Pujara plays it to covers.
Full and on off, Pujara defends it straight back to the bowler. A nice stroke played with a straight bat.
Fuller and outside off, Pujara strokes it towards point.
Now he leaves another length ball outside off this time.
BEAUTY! Josh is making the ball talk here. A length ball in that channel of uncertainity as Pujara looks to defend only to see the ball go past the outside edge.
Length and outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to it now.
Short of good length on off, Kohli blocks it off his back foot as his bottom hand too comes off his bat grip there.
And again he is back to his leaving ways! Length and outside off, Kohli makes a leave. A bit difficult for one who is a natural strokemaker.
Kohli gets underway! Length and on the pads, Virat turns it towards deep square leg and gets a brace to open his account.
Another length ball outside off, Kohli lifts his willow and watches the ball sail through to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and line from Hazlewood, he bowls it on a length and outside off, Pujara makes a calculated leave.
Now a short one but the line is down the leg side from Hazlewood, Pujara sits under it.
Now it is a length ball outside off, Pujara won't find any issue in leaving such deliveries as he does now.
Another inswinger around middle, Pujara turns it towards mid-wicket this time.
Length ball outside off, Pujara raises his bat high up in the air as he makes a leave.
A nip backer from Josh, Pujara who looks to turn it to the leg side but is beaten to get hit high on the thigh pad.
Josh Hazlewood is back into the attack. Paine is shuffling his quicks around. 6-2-14-0 are his figures so far.
Another one which is bowled outside off, VK shoulders arms to this one. A brilliant over from Cummins as he bags a wicket-maiden.
Cummins tries to pepper Kohli with a short one but VK is not interested as he sits under it.
Full and outside off, Kohli has no problems in leaving that one.
On a length and around off, Virat blocks it off the back foot this time.
Full and around off, Kohli strokes it to point.
The skipper, Virat Kohli strides out into the middle now.

OUT! CASTLED! Oh my, oh my! He was looking so good so far and now a bit of lapse in concentration and Agarwal has to depart. Cummins bowls it around off and makes the ball jag back a bit inward. Agarwal, who is lining up for a defensive stroke is done in by the inward movement. The ball just about sneaks in between the gap between the bat and pad to hit the top of off. Brilliant bowling from Cummins, he was constantly bowling that testing line and finally he has his man.
A yorker on off, Pujara strokes it to the left of Starc who fields it.
Full and angled into the pads, Che flicks it straight to the man at mid on now.
Make that 21 as he leaves another one which is bowled way outside off by Starc.
On a good length and around off, Pujara stands tall and keeps it out off the back foot once again. 20 dots in a row for Pujara.
Fuller once again and on off, Pujara plays the straight drive only for Starc to field it in his followthrough.
Full and angled on off, Agarwal strokes it towards covers and takes a single this time.
Full and around off, Pujara does well as he stoops low and pushes it towards point.
On a length and around off, it comes a bit quicker too as Pujara blocks it out off the back foot.
Another good bumper from Cummins, Pujara ducks under it.
Length and on off, Pujara stands tall and blocks it down the track towards the bowler.
This time Pujara does not fall in the trap as Cummins bowls a similar line and Pujji makes a leave.
Well bowled by Patto! Bowls one around off and lands it on a length too, Pujara prods forward to block it but is lucky as the ball sails past the outside edge.
Full and angled into the pads, Agarwal helps it towards deep square leg and scampers for a brace.
Short of good length around off this time. A bit of bounce too as Agarwal hops and defends it.
Good length and around off, Agarwal hops and defends it to the off side.
Bumper down the leg side, Agarwal sits under it.
On off, Agarwal drives it to mid off this time.
FOUR! Uppish! Starc angles one on off from round the wicket, Agarwal lofts it over covers and fetches a boundary now. It was a risky stroke as it could have gone straight up in the air too.
On a length and on middle, Pujara blocks it off the back foot towards mid-wicket. 3 maidens in a row.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar taps it towards point and looks for a single but is rightly sent back by Agarwal there.
Another length ball around off, Pujara keeps it out towards short leg.
Fuller and around off, Pujara blocks it off the front foot.
Now a short one for Che, Pujara arches a bit and then lets the ball sail through. He does well to drop his wrists here.
Good length ball on off, Pujara hops and blocks it off the back foot towards the leg side.
Length ball around the 4th stump line, Agarwal watches it and then raises his bat to give a safe passage for the ball to sail into the mitts of the keeper.
Now Starc tries to test Mayank with a bumper but Agarwal ducks under it.
On a length and in line with the stumps, Agarwal hops and keeps it out to the off side.
Length ball angled across the right-hander, Agarwal lifts his bat and makes a leave.
Oh that's nice from Starc! Pitched on a length and in that channel outside off, Agarwal decides to leave it at the last instance. A brave call that one though as it was very close to the off pole.
On a fuller length and around off, Agarwal drives it off his front foot towards short cover.
Good length on off, Pujara is solid in blocking this one out.
On off, pushed to the leg side.
On a shortish length and on off, Pujara blocks this to the off side and looks for the run again but they do not go for it.
On off, dabbed to point. They are looking for the single but decide that it is not the best plan and decide to not go for the run.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! A good length ball on off, Pujara looks for the defensive stroke but he misses it.

DRINKS! A brilliant first hour for Australia. Right from the word go, they were spot on. Starc was on fire from ball one as he made the pink cherry talk and that resulted in Shaw losing his wicket. Hazlewood and Cummins too have been good. For India, Pujara and Agarwal have held fort together as they have negotiated well. It remains to be seen how the next hour pans out before the tea break.
Short ball outside off, Mayank lets this one through.
Good shot and good running by the batters! A good length ball on off, Pujara punches this one through mid on and collects three runs.
Solid block by Pujara to this short of a length delivery around off.
Short of a length and on off, Pujara is solid in his defense.
On middle, tucked to the mid-wicket region.
Short ball and on off, CP sways away and leaves it.
On off, CP looks to block this one but it takes the edge and goes to the leg side for a single.
The ball is outside the off stump and Pujara decides that he does not want to have a poke at this.
Good length ball and on off, pushed to the mid on region.
On off, tapped to point. A loud and clear no for the single by Cheteshwar.
On off, tucked to the man at short leg.
A good length ball on off, Pujara looks to have a poke at this but gets beaten.
Pat Cummins comes into the attack.

FOUR! CREAMED! On a fuller length and around off, Agarwal comes on the front foot and drives it through covers off the full face of the bat. The ball races to the fence at deep cover for the first boundary of the game.
On a good length and around off, Agarwal tucks it towards short leg.
On a length ball on off, Agarwal pushes it towards point.
On a good length and around off, Agarwal sees the ball and then lets it sail through.
Another one targetting the stumps, Pujara plays it with the straight bat towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Fuller and around middle, Pujara blocks it towards the leg side.
Three to end the over! A good length ball and on off, Pujara drives this wide of the man at mid off and by the time, the fielder can go to the deep and collect it, the batters take three runs.
On off, blocked.
On the pads this time, Pujara tucks this to the leg side. Lyon is the man, who is the leg slip and he makes a dive but it goes past him into the deep. Two runs.
On the body, pushed to the leg side.
Short ball outside off, CP does not engage.
On the pads, tucked to the fine leg region for one.
On off, pushed to the cover region.
Back of a length ball on off and middle, CP leaves it alone.
On middle, defended.

EDGY! Just short of the man at the slips and Pujara gets handed a lifeline. A good length ball and on off, Pujara looks to fend this one out but it takes the outside edge and lands just short of the second and third slip. The ball goes through towards the third man region for a couple. It is also a No Ball as Josh had overstepped.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, Pujara blocks this one to point. 'No, No' is the call from Pujara to Mayank, as the latter was thinking about the single.
Back of a length outside off, CP does not want to have a piece of this and lets it through to Paine.
A full ball outside off, MA does not engage at this one.
Another good length ball on off, another leave by Agarwal.
Short and on off, Mayank sways away and does not engage.
Short of a length outside off, Mayank lets it through.
Outside off, left alone.

That was in the air but the man at short leg is not able to catch it. A back of a length ball on the body, Agarwal looks to block this one out to the leg side but does so towards short leg. The ball lands just in front of the man there. A half-chance for the hosts.
Length on off, Pujara safely negotiates this to the mid on region.
On off, CP looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and goes to the leg side.

Pujara just took his eye of the ball for the second and got hit on the body! A back of a length ball on middle and leg, Pujara looks to move away but does not do so in time and gets hit on the back. Must have stung but nothing serious.
Length and on off, Pujara plays this to the cover region.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length delivery outside off, Pujara raises his willow and leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone by Mayank.
Some extra bounce this time around. A shortish ball and on off, Agarwal hops and does well to fend this one.
On the pads this time, Pujara hops and tucks this to the man at fine leg. A single.
Short of a length delivery on middle and leg, Pujara defends this one out.
On middle, worked to the leg side for a single.
Good leave by Mayank! Length ball outside off, Agarwal raises his blade to let this one through.
BEATEN! Good bowling by Josh! A back of a length ball outside off, CP looks to fend this one out but it whizzes past his outside edge and into the keeper's mitts.

Good fielding in the deep from Wade! A good length ball on off, Agarwal punches this one through the cover-point region and Wade gives it a chase. He does well to dive and keep this one out from the ropes. The batters collect three runs.
Bumper! This is a short ball on middle, Mayank ducks under this one.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length on off, pushed to covers again.
On off, pushed to covers.
Another full ball around off, Pujara strokes this one to the man at short cover. Another good over by Starc.
A full ball, on off, Cheteshwar pushes this to point.
Short of a length outside off, CP looks to defend but misses.
Agarwal opens his account for this game! A good length ball and on off, Mayank pushes it through cover-point for one.

EDGY AGAIN! Excellent start from the bowlers! A back of a length ball on off, Agarwal looks to defend this one but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the point region but luckily for Mayank, it lands safe. India has a nervy start to this game.
BEATEN! A good length ball on off, it moves away from the right-hander, Mayank looks to block this one out but misses it altogether.
A maiden to start off for Hazlewood! A good length ball outside off, CP raises his blade and lets this one through to the keeper.
Bowls it full and on off this time, Pujara pushes this towards covers and is quick to call no for the single.
A full ball down the leg side, Pujara looks for the tuck away but misses.
Another good length ball outside off, Pujara does not think twice in leaving this one alone.
Outside off, Pujara lets this one through.

An appeal for LBW but it is turned down! A back of a length ball on middle and leg, Pujara looks to block this one out but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal follows but nothing from the umpire. Looked to be too high.
Who will it be with the ball from the other end? Josh Hazlewood, it will be with the ball from the other end.

A dot to end the first over! A full ball on off, nipping into the right-hander, Agarwal looks to push this one away but it takes the inside edge and hits the pads to roll to the off side. A brilliant start for the Aussies. Just a single and the wicket from the first over.
Good length outside off, Agarwal leaves this one alone.

EDGY! So close yet so far for Starc to get his second scalp right in the first over! A good length ball on off, Pujara look to block this one out but it kisses the outside edge and goes in between the keeper and first slip on the bounce. The batters sneak in a run and India open their account in this game.
Back of a length ball and on off, Pujara blocks this one out.
Cheteswar Pujara, India's reliable batsman walks out to bat at no. 3 after just two balls into the game.

OUT! CASTLED! DRAGGED ON! Australia draw first blood in this game and Shaw walks back after scoring a 2-ball duck! There were a lot of questions about his inclusion in the squad and he has not answered those questions well. Not what Kohli would have hoped for when he decided to bat first. Starc bowls a good length ball around off, some inward movement noticed, Shaw looks to block this one out but it takes the inside edge and goes onto rattle the stumps behind him. Just the start that the hosts would have wanted to this series.
Starc starts off with a back of a length ball on off, Shaw is solid in blocking this one out.

Time for the National Anthems now. First it will be India's Jana-Gana-Mana followed by Australia's Advance Australia Fair. Done and dusted. We are all set to begin the Pink Ball Test. The two Indian openers, Mayank Agarwal and Prithvi Shaw are out in the middle. After a few words of wisdom from Tim Paine, the Australian players too take their respective positions out on the field. It will be Mitchell Starc first up with the ball. Here we go...
Australia (Playing XI) - Joe Burns, Matthew Wade, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Travis Head, Cameron Green, Tim Paine (C/WK), Pat Cummins, Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Josh Hazlewood.

India (Playing XI) - Prithvi Shaw, Mayank Agarwal, Cheteshwar Pujara, Virat Kohli (C), Ajinkya Rahane, Hanuma Vihari, Wriddhiman Saha (WK), Ravichandran Ashwin, Umesh Yadav, Mohammed Shami, Jasprit Bumrah.

Australian skipper, Tim Paine says that Cameron Green gets his debut and Matthew Wade will open with Joe Burns. He says that there have been a few injury concerns but they are well set. Mentions that they would have batted first but with a quality attack who can perform in all conditions, their bowlers are ready to go out and perform.

The skipper of India, Virat Kohli starts by saying that it looks like a nice wicket and runs on the board is priceless, more so away from home. Hopes that he can apply some pressure on them. Adds that they have prepared really well and the boys have also played a couple of tour games and things have been clear at their end. Feels that playing in the pink test the first time back in India, was not that strangle and adds that the evening session will be slightly harder since it is a pink ball test. Tells that he just wants to help the team win and that has always been his mindset.
TOSS - The men who matter, Tim Paine and Virat Kohli are out in the middle for the all important toss. Up goes the coin and it lands in the favour of Virat Kohli. INDIA WILL BAT FIRST!

Pitch Report - Glenn McGrath says that there is enough grass on the surface and with the weather expected to be hot, it is a win the toss and bat first wicket. Sanjay Manjrekar says that how the pitch behaves in the first 30 mins is crucial and he says that there is no doubt about it, win the toss and bat first.

India, on the other hand, are confident as they have announced their playing XI ahead of the match day. Inclusion of Prithvi Shaw and Wriddhiman Saha ahead of Shubman Gill and Rishabh Pant has raised a lot of eyebrows.  The other cause of concern is that Virat Kohli's absence after the first game could prove to be vital in the grand scheme of the series and so, India would hope to take the early advantage with their skipper's presence.The biggest question that arises is who will break the ice? The answers will start to unfold as we bring you the toss and team updates shortly.

Talking about the Aussies, Steven Smith's availability after having a sore back was a cause of concern but it seems that he will be fit to take part in the first test. It also looks like Cameron Green will make his Test debut for the hosts. They will certainly miss the services of David Warner who had been ruled out of the encounter due to an injury. Their attack with the ball seems to be in sync as their gun bowlers will all be rearing to have a go at this Indian batting line-up. A win to start the Test series will be on the minds of the hosts.

After being even-stevens at the end of the white ball leg, the bandwagon now moves to the Test series. After the white ball, now it's time for the pink ball. Though, Australia hold the upper hand with the pink kookaburra as they have won 7 out of 7 games compared to their counter-parts who have just played 1 game under the lights, it still looks to be an interesting contest that will unfold.

Right. 8 overs left in the day but don't think we will get all 8. We would be lucky to get 5. Australia will hope for at least a wicket or two while India will aim to knock these off without any damage. The players come out to the middle. Prithvi Shaw and Mayank Agarwal are the openers for India. It is Mitchell Starc with the new strawberry. The man on a pair, Shaw, will face. Here we go...
